docs.abstract: The president’s “I accomplished the military” claim makes a strange kind of sense in articulating the relationship between the president and troops, one expert says.
docs.snippet: The president’s “I accomplished the military” claim makes a strange kind of sense in articulating the relationship between the president and troops, one expert says.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Over the past two weeks, President Trump has repeatedly boasted of being a boon for the military. He has trumpeted the Pentagon’s $700 billion budget, taken credit for staving off a “major war” with North Korea and generally declared victory on all things related to the United States’ armed forces.

headline.main: Mission ‘Accomplished’? Trump Boasts of Being Boon for Military
headline.print_headline: Trump ‘Accomplished The Military,’ He Says. But Experts Disagree.
